  <refnamediv id='name'>
    <refname>ipsec-ondemand</refname>
    <refpurpose>Add and route a connection</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <!-- body begins here -->
  <refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>ipsec ondemand</command>
      <arg choice='plain'><replaceable>connection</replaceable></arg>
      <arg choice='opt'>--config <replaceable>@@IPSEC_CONF@@</replaceable></arg>
      <arg choice='opt'>--ctlsocket <replaceable>@@RUNDIR@@/pluto.ctl</replaceable></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1 id='description'>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      <command>ipsec ondemand</command> is equivalent to running first
      <command>ipsec add
      <replaceable>connection</replaceable></command> and then
      <command>ipsec route
      <replaceable>connection</replaceable></command>, causing the
      same effect as connection configuration option
      <option>auto=ondemand</option>. This sets up connection to be
      <option>on demand</option>, causing connection to establish only
      when triggered by outbound traffic.
    </para>
    <para>
      Note: you might also need to run <command>ipsec
      rereadsecrets</command> when your new connection uses pre-shared
      key (PSK) authentication, <option>authby=secret</option> because
      secrets keys are only being read at startup.
    </para>
  </refsect1>

